  <title>
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">Nepal - CEN - Earthquake Response and Recovery in Sindhupalchowk</narrative>
  </title>
  <description type="1">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">1000 households will be benefit from temporary shelter.

1000 households will benefit from Livelihood and WASH Intervention depending upon the needs and priorities.

&#x2022;  Focus Group Discussions with communities and local engineers, masons and carpenters to discuss transitional shelter and the up-coming harsh weather. 
&#x2022; Rapid Needs Assessment 
&#x2022; Building of Transitional shelters
&#x2022; Cash will be distributed to those who have already built their temporary shelter either by themselves or by loan. 
&#x2022; Training on WASH will be carried out with children and women
&#x2022; Support communities with building improved cooking stoves, water supply, solar lighting, toilets 
&#x2022; Support communities to uplift the livelihoods and their capacity to rebuild permanent shelter.</narrative>
  </description>
  <description type="2">
   <narrative xml:lang="EN">&#x2022; 125 community members trained in building transitional shelter
&#x2022; Community constructed transitional shelters for 1000 families to provide adequate protection from the environment; monsoon rains, wind, high temperatures, low temperatures
&#x2022; 4000 community members have access to clean and safe drinking water, proper sanitation and hygiene
&#x2022; Livelihood for 1000 affected families improved while increasing their resilience to disaster</narrative>
  </description>
